public abstract class NodeEngine
extends Engine

Linkable Engine.

Fundamental design inside WUIC is to use a set of NodeEngine to be executed. They are structured using the chain of responsibility design pattern. Each engine is in charge of the execution of the next engine and could decide not to execute it.

Method Detail

chain

public static NodeEngine chain(NodeEngine... engines)

Link the given engines. They will be linked respecting the order of the implied by their Engine.getEngineType().

If an NodeEngine is already chained to other engines, any engine won't be added as the next engine but to the end of the existing chain.

If two different instances of the same class appear in the chain, then the first one will be replaced by the second one, keeping the original position.

Parameters:
engines - the engines
Returns:
the first engine of the given array
